Use a small square cardboard box to make the table as follows:
Remove any of the top flaps from the box. Leave the bottom flaps intact––these will be the top of the table shortly. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/a/a5/Make-a-Restaurant-for-Your-American-Girl-Doll-Step-2Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Restaurant-for-Your-American-Girl-Doll-Step-2Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/a/a5/Make-a-Restaurant-for-Your-American-Girl-Doll-Step-2Bullet1.jpg/aid4039945-v4-728px-Make-a-Restaurant-for-Your-American-Girl-Doll-Step-2Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Turn the box upside down. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/d/d6/Make-a-Restaurant-for-Your-American-Girl-Doll-Step-2Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Restaurant-for-Your-American-Girl-Doll-Step-2Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/d/d6/Make-a-Restaurant-for-Your-American-Girl-Doll-Step-2Bullet2.jpg/aid4039945-v4-728px-Make-a-Restaurant-for-Your-American-Girl-Doll-Step-2Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Draw arches of the same size on each side of the box. Do not draw them to the edges though––stop them about 1inch or 2.5cm from each edge and the top of the box. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/7f/Make-a-Restaurant-for-Your-American-Girl-Doll-Step-2Bullet3.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Restaurant-for-Your-American-Girl-Doll-Step-2Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/7/7f/Make-a-Restaurant-for-Your-American-Girl-Doll-Step-2Bullet3.jpg/aid4039945-v4-728px-Make-a-Restaurant-for-Your-American-Girl-Doll-Step-2Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Cut out each arch. You should be left with four legs that use the box corners and the tabletop still intact. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/11/Make-a-Restaurant-for-Your-American-Girl-Doll-Step-2Bullet4.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Restaurant-for-Your-American-Girl-Doll-Step-2Bullet4.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/1/11/Make-a-Restaurant-for-Your-American-Girl-Doll-Step-2Bullet4.jpg/aid4039945-v4-728px-Make-a-Restaurant-for-Your-American-Girl-Doll-Step-2Bullet4.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Paint or cover the table with paper or a tablecloth. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/9/9b/Make-a-Restaurant-for-Your-American-Girl-Doll-Step-2Bullet5.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Restaurant-for-Your-American-Girl-Doll-Step-2Bullet5.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/9/9b/Make-a-Restaurant-for-Your-American-Girl-Doll-Step-2Bullet5.jpg/aid4039945-v4-728px-Make-a-Restaurant-for-Your-American-Girl-Doll-Step-2Bullet5.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}
